summary:
David Tennant, Michael Sheen & Neil Gaiman To Attend NYCC Good Omens Panel

  

Just announced - David Tennant, Michael Sheen...
caption:
David Tennant, Michael Sheen & Neil Gaiman To Attend NYCC Good Omens Panel

Just announced - David Tennant, Michael Sheen and Neil Gaiman will be participating in panel for the upcoming Amazon Studios series Good Omens at New York Comic Con next month. The hugely anticipated adaptation of the cult fantasy novel, written by Neil Gaiman in collaboration with the late Sr Terry Pratchett, hits Amazon Prime worldwide in early 2019, with scripts written by Gaiman himself, who also acts as showrunner for the six part series.

Read more here

body:
Rose City CC Day 2

While I’m waiting at the clinic for a doctor, I thought I’d write this. So…

*Hanging out with @elsinore-and-inverness!

*Meeting Catherine Tate!

*Catherine Tate loving my design so much that she took pictures of it on her phone and gave me a free autograph *fangirls all over again*

*Getting squished by John Barrowman (he said “come here for a cuddle” and I swear I was still shaking half an hour later)

*Talking to DT a bit

*DT saying “hello again” in my DT/JB Photo op, though I’m pretty sure he only said that because I took a photo with him half an hour earlier and not because he actually recognised me

*Finding Stargate stuff in the con!

*Just watching DT signing and watching his faces as he talked to people

*Being sandwiched between David Tennant and John Barrowman

OhMyGallifrey!!

I have a biiiiig theory for you if your interested!

What if when the 10th Doctor and Martha got transported to the weeping angels…that was the point in his timeline that made the year a fixed point! It probably only got reeeaalyy turned into the fixed point in time at Lake silencio after his first death (when River actually shot him the first time) ….or I’m probably crazy and reading into the year 1969 too much…maybe….probably……..yes.
